                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d125">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/148<hi rend="superscript"
                    >1/12</hi>: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-29T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 29, 1940—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>52. From the Under Secretary. Your 68, May 24, 8 p.m. Captain B. L. Canaga, U. S.
                    Navy, and Lieutenant Colonel A. R. Harris, U. S. Army, have been designated by
                    their respective Departments to undertake the proposed conversations in Quito
                    with the Ecuadorean authorities. …</p>
                <p>They are proceeding direct to Santiago by Panagra plane and following the
                    termination of their conversations there will proceed to Lima and Quito. You
                    will be advised in advance through the Embassy in Lima of the exact date of
                    their arrival in Quito. [Welles.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
